        "content": "I’ve completed the requested process for tour J09B:\n\n1. Created a temporary table `J09B_temp` with all `decision_table` rows where `TOUR` starts with `J09B`, and added the `ENTSCHEIDUNG` column.\n2. Classified each house:\n   - Counted `EQUNR` per `HAUS`.\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'KSA'` if a house has fewer than 3 `EQUNR`.\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'EVU'` otherwise.\n   - Overrode this so that any row with `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` is always `EVU`.\n3. Enriched the data:\n   - Joined with `eablg` using `ANLAGE` = `Installation` to bring in `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`.\n   - Joined with `sales_master` and `net_master` using `EQUNR`.\n   - When both sales and net records exist, used the contact data from `sales_master` and left the net fields unused; if only net exists, used the net data.\n4. Exported the final result to a CSV named `J09B.csv` with exactly these columns:  \n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.  \n   - 20,180 rows were exported.\n5. Sent the CSV to the EVU team at `meter.readings@evu.com` with an explanatory email.\n6. Dropped the temporary table `J09B_temp` from the database.\n\nIf you’d like, I can also generate a brief summary report (e.g., how many houses were classified as KSA vs EVU).",
